## Data retention — hot / warm / cold (ADR-006)

**SSOT:** [DECISIONS.md ADR-006](../../DECISIONS.md#adr-006--hot--warm--cold-data-tiers) · [dev-docs/DATA_RETENTION_PLAN.md](../../dev-docs/DATA_RETENTION_PLAN.md)

- **Hot (2y, UI reads):** `daily_ops_snapshot*` + `daily_ops_revenue_benchmark` only on Revenue / Daily Ops GET paths.
- **Warm (2y):** `bork_business_days`, `eitje_time_registration_aggregation`. Fat `bork_sales_by_*` = pipeline buffer — **delete per day after snapshot sealed**.
- **Cold:** Bork + Eitje **shift** raw → DO Spaces blob → delete from Mongo. Eitje master-data (`users`, `teams`, `environments`) stays in Mongo.
- **60d** = benchmark precompute + backfill SLA (not a delete cutoff). **90d** = optional Mongo grace for shift drill-down.
- **Never** read-time Bork/Eitje aggregation on Revenue overview (ADR-004 + ADR-006). Missing snapshot → partial / backfill queue.
- New archive/purge/revenue-read code: **`@adr-ref: ADR-006`** in metadata header + update `@exports-to`.

